<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="284" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1158,1183]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pleurae without a dark strip below the postpronotum and wing base (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1186,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,656,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,625,1931]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 24. Habitus, lateral view; 25. Thorax, dorsal view; 26. Head, frontal view; 27. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594982/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Epandrium with few setulae in a small squared ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[626,715,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Surstylus bearing 6 peg-like prensisetae, without a crescent process above them (
<figureCitation box="[387,472,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus bearing small scales when in lateral and dorsal views (
<figureCitation box="[1219,1356,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Figs. 31–33</figureCitation>
). Apex of aedeagus ventrally projected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="285" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1302,1327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Description</emphasis>
. 
<specimenCount box="[354,378,1303,1326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Head (
<figureCitation box="[468,608,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,656,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,625,1931]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 24. Habitus, lateral view; 25. Thorax, dorsal view; 26. Head, frontal view; 27. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594982/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Figs. 26–27</figureCitation>
). Yellow. Frons and face yellow, fronto-orbital plates indistinct with the same color of the front. Length ratio of mid to anterior orbital setae = 0.30 (0.27–0.33), length ratio of mid to posterior orbital setae = 0.32 (0.27–0.37), vt index = 0.90 (0.80–1.00), ocellar triangle yellowish about 25% (22– 28%) of frontal length. Facial carina not prominent with the same color of the frons. Antennae yellow with flagellomeres slightly grey, aristae with 4–5 dorsal and one ventral branches, plus terminal fork. Palpus yellowish with an apical setae and two or three smaller preapical setae. Red eyes with short piles. Gena yellow, first genal setae about 26% (25–27%) of the vibrissae length. Cheek index = 0.22 (0.21–0.24), eye index = 1.01 (1.00–1.03).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[298,439,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,656,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,625,1931]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 24. Habitus, lateral view; 25. Thorax, dorsal view; 26. Head, frontal view; 27. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594982/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Figs. 24–25</figureCitation>
). Main color yellow. Length = 0.63 (0.53–0.70) mm, width = 0.46 (0.44–0.48) mm, 6 irregular rows of acrostichal, no prescutellar setae. Dc index = 0.50 (0.45–0.55). Scutellum yellowish. Basal scutellar setae convergent. Scut position index = 0.66 (0.63–0.70). Two prominent katepisternal setae and a row of setulae between them. Anterior katepisternal about 37% (32–41%) of the posterior one. Pleurae and legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
Wings (
<figureCitation box="[287,372,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–47" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[183,1382,1239,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,1210,1902]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 44–47. Wings. 44. H. rondonia sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 45. H. nungara sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 46. H. jukyry sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 47. H. crioula sp. nov., holotype, ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594990/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Yellow with veins dark yellow. Length = 1.28 (1.14–1.42) mm. Length to width ratio = 0.62 (0.60–0.65). Indices: C = 1.37 (1.32–1.42); 
<date box="[639,667,1735,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">4v</date>
= 1.83 (1.73–1.93); 
<date box="[897,925,1734,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">5x</date>
= 2.58 (2.50–2.66); 4c = 1.36 (1.33–1.40); M = 0.60 (0.53–0.66); hb = 1.75 (1.60–1.90); prox. x = 0.33 (0.33–0.33).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Abdomen. Main color yellow. Tergites II–V with posterior fainted brown marginal bands not reaching lateral area.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" box="[199,474,1878,1903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
Body length = 
<quantity box="[366,469,1878,1903]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.50 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,906,2011]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="285" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[335,473,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Figs. 28–33</figureCitation>
). Epandrium microtrichose, smaller than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[965,1254,1915,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondonia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[965,1254,1915,1939]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Hirtodrosophila rondonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1261,1351,1914,1939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1261,1351,1914,1939]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, with 6 upper and 10 lower setae, 4 of the latter located on ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[921,1009,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Ventral lobe not microtrichose, not covering the surstylus. Cerci not fused with epandrium, microtrichose. Surstylus not microtrichose, with 6 peg-like prensisetae, about 5 inner and no outer setae. Decasternum narrow (
<figureCitation box="[919,1004,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium longer than epandrium, without a posterior hypandrial process; gonopod fused to hypandrium, each bearing one seta (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1295,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,213,1896]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 28–33. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 28. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 29. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 30. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 31–33. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594984/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Paraphysis microtrichose, with two small setulae. Aedeagus bearing small scales dorsally and laterally, apical region with a projection easier to recognize in lateral view, when in ventral view the lateral margin presents a serrated aspect. Aedeagal apodeme fused with and longer than aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,352,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">
<specimenCount box="[199,221,333,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,357,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">Relationship.</emphasis>
The male terminalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[626,730,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jukyry" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[626,730,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">H. jukyry</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[737,827,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[737,827,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Patterson &amp; Wheeler" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[988,1092,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis box="[988,1092,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">H. grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D." box="[1151,1319,367,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref6796" refString="Grimaldi, D. (2018) Hirtodrosophila of North America (Diptera: Drosophilidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 421, 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 421.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Grimaldi 2018</bibRefCitation>
), differing by the smaller surstylus, the lower number of inner bristles and the absence of the crescent process. The aedeagus of these species is quite similar too, varying mainly in the shape of the apex in dorsoventral view (rounded in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Patterson &amp; Wheeler" baseAuthorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">H. grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the absence of the ventral scales in the apical region (as presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D." box="[1045,1229,476,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="285" pagination="1 - 75" refId="ref6796" refString="Grimaldi, D. (2018) Hirtodrosophila of North America (Diptera: Drosophilidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 421, 1 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 421.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Grimaldi (2018)</bibRefCitation>
in 
<figureCitation box="[1268,1370,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1408,656,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,625,1931]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Hirtodrosophila jukyry sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 24. Habitus, lateral view; 25. Thorax, dorsal view; 26. Head, frontal view; 27. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594982/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="285">Fig. 25B</figureCitation>
, page 421), and being shorter than the aedeagal apodeme. Despite the great similitude regarding the male terminalia, the body morphology and coloration is very different.
</paragraph>
